HEADWORD: Ropeband
<hw>Rope"band`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A small piece of spun yarn or marline, used to fasten the head of
the sail to the spar.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>roband</asp>, and
<asp>robbin</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ropedancer</ent>⟦br⟧
